title: Drone footage captures untouched Iceland landscapes
text:
Drone footage captures untouched Iceland landscapes Last updated 13:28, October 8 2015 YouTube.com/Luke Skyvideo 
Drone footage captures the beauty of Iceland 
≈Åukasz Ciechanowski used a drone to capture the mesmerising landscapes of Iceland. 
The footage sweeps across vast glacial valleys, thundering waterfalls and untouched areas of the European country. 
Drones are changing the face of travel videography. They allow people to explore never before seen landscapes from land, sea and air. Reuters/SCREENGRAB 
Iceland is breathtaking from land and air. 
The breathtaking footage was captured in various locations around the country. 
Have you been to Iceland? What were your thoughts in the country? Tell us in comments.
